modules.description: This module provides functions for parsing and pretty-printing network-related data structures, particularly firewall rules with components like actions, protocols, and IP prefixes. It operates on low-level packet filter configurations, handling elements such as CIDR notation, port ranges, ICMP types, and domain-based destinations. The tools are designed for use in network security contexts, such as validating or transforming QubesOS firewall policies into structured representations.

This module parses and pretty-prints network data structures, focusing on firewall rules with actions, protocols, and IP prefixes. It handles low-level packet filter configurations, including CIDR, port ranges, ICMP types, and domain-based destinations. Designed for network security tasks like validating or transforming QubesOS firewall policies into structured formats.
